'''Kotohira Shrine''' (金刀比羅神社) is a {{ill|Shinto|ja|神道}} shrine located in {{ill|Shirahama Town|ja|白浜町}}, Nishimuro District, Wakayama Prefecture.

== Deities ==
; Main Deities
* {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大己貴命}}
* {{ill|Kotoshironushi|ja|事代主命}}
* 8 other deities

== History ==
According to shrine records, the shrine was established in 1836 (Tenpō 7) when local residents invited the deity of {{ill|Kotohira Shrine (Kagawa)|ja|金刀比羅宮}} from {{ill|Sanuki Province|ja|讃岐国}}. During the {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治時代}}, it was merged with the nearby gōsha, Nissha Shrine, as part of the {{ill|Shrine Consolidation Policy|ja|神社合祀}}. However, due to persistent requests from local residents, the shrine was reinstated in 1911 (Meiji 44) with approval from the Wakayama Prefectural Office.<ref>[http://www.minakata.org/relatedspot/minakatamandalanofukeichi/kotohirajinjya/ Kotohira Shrine | Minakata Kumagusu Archives]</ref>

{{ill|Minakata Kumagusu|ja|南方熊楠}} documented the reinstatement process in his "Opinion on Shrine Mergers." He noted that the priest of the merged shrine attempted to retain the Kotohira Shrine's deity, hiding the sacred object from the residents. However, the object given to the merged shrine was a counterfeit, and the true sacred object, secretly kept by the residents, facilitated the shrine's restoration. This anecdote remains a significant part of the shrine's history.

== Information ==
; Location
* Wakayama Prefecture, Nishimuro District, Shirahama Town, Chūaza Tori-no-Kura 1702

; Access
* Nearest bus stop: JR {{ill|Kisei Main Line|ja|紀勢本線}} {{ill|Kii-Tonda Station|ja|紀伊富田駅}}, followed by an 18-minute walk southwest (approximately 1.4 km).

