'''Kotohira Shrine''' (金刀比羅神社) is a {{ill|Shinto|ja|神道|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto|qq=}} shrine located in {{ill|Shirahama, Wakayama|ja|白浜町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shirahama, Wakayama|qq=}}.

== Deities ==
; Main Deities
* {{ill|Ōkuninushi|ja|大己貴命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōkuninushi|qq=}}
* {{ill|Kotoshironushi|ja|事代主命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshironushi|qq=}}
* 8 other deities

== History ==
According to shrine records, the shrine was established in 1836 (Tenpō 7) when local residents invited the deity of {{ill|Kotohira-gū|ja|金刀比羅宮|1=Kotohira-gū|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotohira-gū|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotohira-gū|qq=}} from {{ill|Sanuki Province|ja|讃岐国|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sanuki Province|qq=}}. During the {{ill|Meiji period|ja|明治|lt=Meiji period|1=Meiji era|2=ja|3=明治|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji period|qq=}}, it was merged with the nearby gōsha, Nissha Shrine, as part of the {{ill|Shrine Consolidation Policy|ja|神社合祀|1=Shrine Consolidation Policy|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shrine Consolidation Policy|13=User:Immanuelle/Shrine Consolidation Policy|qq=}}. However, due to persistent requests from local residents, the shrine was reinstated in 1911 (Meiji 44) with approval from the Wakayama Prefectural Office.<ref>[http://www.minakata.org/relatedspot/minakatamandalanofukeichi/kotohirajinjya/ Kotohira Shrine | Minakata Kumagusu Archives]</ref>

{{ill|Minakata Kumagusu|ja|南方熊楠|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Minakata Kumagusu|qq=}} documented the reinstatement process in his "Opinion on Shrine Mergers." He noted that the priest of the merged shrine attempted to retain the Kotohira Shrine's deity, hiding the sacred object from the residents. However, the object given to the merged shrine was a counterfeit, and the true sacred object, secretly kept by the residents, facilitated the shrine's restoration. This anecdote remains a significant part of the shrine's history.

